## Inferential Statistics

Each inferential statistic will give us:

-   Test statistic

    -   $r,t,F,\chi^2...$

-   p-value: probability of committing a Type 1 Error \< 0.05 or 5%

    -   p \> 0.05: Fail to reject the $H_0$

    -   p \< 0.05: Reject $H_0$

