## Does bedtime phone use affect sleep?

> **Design Summary**  
80 students from XYZ University took part in a study on sleep and cell phone use. Participants were randomly assigned to one of two conditions. One group was instructed to avoid phone use for 30 minutes before bed, while the other used their phones as normal. The next morning, all students rated their sleep quality on a 1â€“10 scale.  

- **IV**: Phone use before bed (Yes vs. No)  
- **DV**: Sleep quality rating (1 = poor, 10 = excellent)  
- **Design**: Between-subjects, randomized  

